snippet.textDisplay:
I met my now fiance and we used to listen to mac's watching movies with the sound off everyday. Since then we have listened to every album on the release day. We've cried, laughed and just genuinely smiled over all his music.
Almost 3 years ago 2 of my family members drowned. I listened to mac everyday and cried and laughed and smiled.
When he passed it killed me. Knowing I'd never see him in concert. My fiance was in the middle of ordering me swimming tickets for my birthday when we found out.
Since then, we welcomed out daughter into the world. Ever since she was born she's been so happy. When she cried or couldnt sleep we played wings for her. It always made her relaxed.
Listening to circles she danced and smiled continously throughout the entire album.
His music has literally changed my life and I will listen to it till the day I die.
I love this guy. I miss him so much and I really wish I could just thank his family for putting this out.

After listening to the album, I believe Mac made peace with moving on. I know people who have lived a full life and still aren't ready. No one is ready to die. But it is much easier when you're at peace when the time comes.

snippet.textDisplay:
Dear mister Mac Miller

I’ve been writing music of my own for 9 years. It was because of artists like you that I believed what I was doing was a good thing for others around me. It was your music and a few others that helped level me and keep me happy. And knowing that my music could one day do just that, motivated me every day. Thank you so much you beautiful soul. Rest easy ❤️

One of your proudest fans ~
Z.
snippet.textOriginal:
Dear mister Mac Miller

   I’ve been writing music of my own for 9 years. It was because of artists like you that I believed what I was doing was a good thing for others around me. It was your music and a few others that helped level me and keep me happy. And knowing that my music could one day do just that, motivated me every day. Thank you so much you beautiful soul. Rest easy ❤️

    One of your proudest fans ~
                  Z.
